From a96791ecc6b130374eff2d59099d0eba0bb8c0fd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 11:46:10 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [DOSKUTSU] djgpp: disable fmt's locale code path to dodge
 ctype-macro collision
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Symptom: 'make nxengine' fails inside fmt's bundled base.h while
parsing misc.cpp's TU:

  deps/spdlog/fmt/bundled/base.h:930:43:
    error: macro "isalpha" passed 2 arguments, but takes just 1
    detail::ignore_unused(isalpha('x', loc));

Cause: DJGPP's <ctype.h> defines isalpha as a 1-arg function-style
macro (`#define isalpha(c) (__dj_ctype_flags[(int)(c)+1] & __dj_ISALPHA)`).
fmt's bundled base.h:930 calls 'isalpha('x', loc)' — the C++
locale-aware 2-arg overload from <locale> + std::ctype facets — inside
its locale_ref template, gated by '#if FMT_USE_LOCALE'. The C
preprocessor doesn't know about the C++ overload and expands the macro
first, collapsing to a 1-arg call site that produces a 2-arg list
under the parens.

Fix: define FMT_USE_LOCALE=0 before '#include <spdlog/fmt/fmt.h>' in
src/Utils/Logger_djgpp.h. fmt provides this knob exactly so users can
opt out of the <locale> code path. Effects:

* Eliminates the unqualified isalpha/isdigit/etc. call sites that fmt
  emits under FMT_USE_LOCALE=1 — no preprocessor collision possible.
* Removes the <locale>-using runtime support fmt would otherwise pull
  in. DJGPP libstdc++ ships <locale> in a stripped form (no
  localedef facets, no UTF awareness on DOS); avoiding it is a small
  binary-size and compile-time win.
* Cave Story has no localized number / time / monetary formatting
  needs anywhere in the codebase. NXEngine's logger doesn't
  parameterize on locale either. Zero functional regression on
  non-DJGPP platforms (this define lives in Logger_djgpp.h which is
  only included under '#ifdef __DJGPP__').

Why DOS needs this: DJGPP libc retains classic-C macro-form ctype.h
for performance reasons (single array lookup beats a function call).
That convention predates C++'s 2-arg locale-overloaded ctype API by
decades; the two cannot coexist in the same TU without one of them
being neutered. fmt's FMT_USE_LOCALE knob is the documented escape
hatch — using it is the cleanest fix.

Alternative considered: '#undef isalpha' (and other ctype macros) in
Logger_djgpp.h's preamble before fmt include. Works but blanket-undefs
macros that might be used elsewhere in the same TU, and leaves fmt's
locale code path active (more code than we need). FMT_USE_LOCALE=0 is
both surgical and reduces footprint.
---
 src/Utils/Logger_djgpp.h | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/Utils/Logger_djgpp.h b/src/Utils/Logger_djgpp.h
index 970fc44..3cd4866 100644
--- a/src/Utils/Logger_djgpp.h
+++ b/src/Utils/Logger_djgpp.h
@@ -32,6 +32,17 @@
 //   * No colour. NXEngine on DOS prints to a single stderr stream where
 //     ANSI escapes would be visible literal noise.
 
+// Disable fmt's <locale>-using code path. fmt's bundled base.h calls
+// `isalpha('x', loc)` (the C++ locale-aware 2-arg overload) inside its
+// locale_ref class template, gated by `#if FMT_USE_LOCALE`. DJGPP's
+// <ctype.h> defines `isalpha` as a 1-arg function-style macro, which the
+// preprocessor expands first — collision: `macro "isalpha" passed 2
+// arguments, but takes just 1`. Setting FMT_USE_LOCALE=0 elides the
+// locale code path entirely. Cave Story is single-locale (C/POSIX) and
+// has no localized number formatting need, so this loses nothing
+// functional. Bonus: skips the heavyweight <locale> include, which
+// DJGPP libstdc++ ships in stripped form anyway.
+#define FMT_USE_LOCALE 0
 #include <spdlog/fmt/fmt.h>
 
 #include <cstdio>
